d1.product.title: D1 SQL Database
d1.beta_description: D1 is currently in Open Beta. To give feedback, visit our <0>D1 Discord channel</0>.
d1.alpha_deprecation: On August 15, 2024, D1 alpha databases will stop accepting live SQL queries. See our <0>migration guide</0> to convert these DBs to use the new production-ready backend.
d1.alpha_db_tooltip: Alpha databases will stop accepting queries on August 15, 2024. Backups will still be available until December 31, 2024.
d1.product_description: Create serverless SQL databases to query relational data.
d1.empty_state: Nothing here yet? Get started by <0>creating your first D1 Database</0>.

d1.db.create.errors.generic: There was a problem creating your database, please try again later.
d1.db.create.errors.limit_reached: You have reached the maximum number of databases (%{dbLimit}) for your account. Please consider deleting unused databases, or visit the <0>D1 documentation</0> to learn more.
d1.db.create.errors.invalid_length: Database name must be less than 250 characters long
d1.db.create.errors.invalid_characters: Database name can only contain lowercase letters (a-z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), and hyphens (-)

d1.db.tabs.tables.empty.title: Your database was successfully created!

d1.db.tabs.time_travel.title: Time Travel

d1.db.tabs.time_travel.empty_state.descr: <0>Visit the documentation</0> to start using Time Travel.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.free_description: Restore your database to any point in time within the past 7 days by choosing a specific time or referencing a bookmark ID.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.paid_description: Restore your database to any point in time within the past 30 days by choosing a specific time or referencing a bookmark ID.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.main.title: Restore an older version of your database using time travel.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.main.button.title: Restore database
Bookmark IDs can be used as an alternative to timestamps when referring to a point in time to restore your database to.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.restore_card.info: Restoring your database to an older version will overwrite your current database.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.restore_card.book: Using a bookmark ID is an alternative to selecting a date and time to restore your database to.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.error_card.info: There was a problem restoring your database, please try again later.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.restoring_card.in: Database restore in progress. We will let you know once it is complete.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.restored_banner.i: Your database has successfully been restored.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.restored_card.inf: This is your unique Bookmark ID for the most recent version of your database before the restore.

<0>Important:</0> This Bookmark ID will not be displayed again after you leave this page. If you think you might need to undo your restore in the future, please copy and securely save this ID now. You can also choose to <1>undo</1> the restore now.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.undoing_card.info: We are undoing your database restore. We will let you know once it is complete.
d1.db.tabs.time_travel.undone_card.info: Your database restore has been undone. You may continue to use your database.

d1.sidebar.metrics.title: Account details
d1.sidebar.read_queries.tooltip: The number of read queries issued against a database. This is the raw number of read queries, and is not used for billing.
d1.sidebar.write_queries.tooltip: The number of write queries issued against a database. This is the raw number of write queries, and is not used for billing.
d1.sidebar.metered_storage.tooltip: The amount of storage your databases have used across time. To learn more visit <0>documentation</0>.
d1.sidebar.rows_read.paid_tooltip: 25 billion rows read per billing cycle are included in your plan for free. To learn more visit <0>documentation</0>.
d1.sidebar.rows_written.paid_tooltip: 50 million rows written per billing cycle are included in your plan for free. To learn more visit <0>documentation</0>.
d1.sidebar.storage_used.paid_tooltip: Current total storage for all databases. To learn more visit <0>documentation</0>.
d1.sidebar.rows_read.free_tooltip: Your account is limited to 5 million rows read per day. To remove this limit, <0>upgrade your plan</0>.
d1.sidebar.rows_written.free_tooltip: Your account is limited to 100,000 rows written per day. To remove this limit, <0>upgrade your plan</0>.
d1.sidebar.storage_used.free_tooltip: Your account is limited to 5 GB of storage. To remove this limit, <0>upgrade your plan</0>.
d1.sidebar.links.wrangler_cli_guide.desc: Manage your database using the Wrangler Command Line Interface (CLI).
